snippet: An aircraft from Naval Air Station Whidbey Island crashed in eastern Washington on Monday morning and all three crew members died, the authorities said.
abstract: Authorities say Navy aircraft from Naval Air Station Whidbey Island crashed in eastern Washington, killing all three crew members.
